title: USGS Library
name: usgs-library
notes: The USGS Library provides the full collection of USGS Series Publications, including specialized data publications and other publications with ancillary data for download or other access methods. In addition, the Library maintains special collections of digital assets such as the USGS Historic Photo Library, providing digital downloads of thousands of historic photos of significance to earth science.

organization.description:
http://www.usgs.gov/
The USGS is a federal science agency that provides impartial information on the health of our ecosystems and environment, the natural hazards that threaten us, the natural resources we rely on, the impacts of climate and land-use change, and the core science systems that help us provide timely, relevant, and useable information.
